@* Content Block — renders raw HTML from DefaultValue.
   Use for headings, paragraphs, instructions, or any custom HTML within the form.
   Any {{ DictionaryKey }} tokens inside the HTML are localized for the current culture.

   SECURITY / TRUST BOUNDARY:
   The content below is emitted verbatim via @Html.Raw, so it is a stored-XSS vector BY DESIGN.
   This is acceptable ONLY because the value can be authored exclusively by trusted backoffice
   users who can manage forms: the form builder / save endpoints are gated behind
   CanCurrentUserManageForms() (Settings-section access), and this DefaultValue is never set
   from an untrusted public submission. Do NOT wire this field's DefaultValue to any anonymous
   or end-user-supplied input. If that trust assumption ever changes, run the value through an
   HTML sanitizer (allow-list) before rendering, or switch to @content (HTML-encoded). *@
@using uTPro.Feature.SimpleFormBuilder.Helpers
@using Umbraco.Cms.Core.Dictionary
@model uTPro.Feature.SimpleFormBuilder.Models.FormFieldViewModel

@if (!string.IsNullOrEmpty(Model.DefaultValue))
{
    var content = FieldHelper.Localize(Model.DefaultValue, ViewData["CultureDictionary"] as ICultureDictionary);
    <div class="uTProForm-content-block @(Model.CssClass ?? "")">
        @Html.Raw(content)
    </div>
}
